<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> As with Greek and Roman practice filiation was a normal part of Carthaginian nomenclature.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Hannibal's date of death is most commonly given as 183 BC, but there is a possibility it could have taken place in 182 BC.</li>
</ol>
